., 532. Enter the money-lender from the direction of the forum (town), i. e. by the stage-door to the right of the spectators. As some little time is supposed to elapse before his entrance he does not see the departing Themopides, who perhaps leaves the stage by the same door (right ; unless we are to infer that he met the vendor of the house at the harbour, cf. 547).
